column12: Measurement condition : Vegetation; Clear  No Precipitation  Moderate Wind Blowing Downstream
column13: Trickle flow at the 90 degree turn 10m d/s of gauge. Vegetation and algae choking the trickle flow channel
column14: Few panel "wade" mmnt. Relatively good quality measurement.   20>panels but shots taken where i could.  Panel Q>10% since only 3 panels.  Tried to clean up section but still some boundary interference. @ Uncertainty: IVE method 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ HG tracking well. HG2 (OTT) confirmed broken and invalid. Flushed both intakes well recovered quickly. Replaced HG2 (OTT) Starting at 8:52.  Must have bumped SE power or similar during OTT set up since huge jump at 9:05.  HG invalid from 9:05 to 9:35. HG2 valid from 9:35 on Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy  No Precipitation  Calm Wind
column13: Control clear. Grass in channel flattened down from high water.
column14: Good wade mmnt 10m u/s gauge at channel constriction. Narrow section so less than 20 panels but best section with minimal veg. Panels >10% but shots taken every 0.1m. Grass at LB made taking a shot at 1.2m impossible tried both regular and reverse shot. Extrapolating with the 1.3m panel more representative. Boundary interference error at LB. MGH Calc @ Uncertainty: IVE method 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ OTT appears to be broken. Block is nose down into gauge pool would like to clean tip of OTT incase its jammed. Gauge pool too deep too access block without pulling rail tie out by the sensor cable. SE switched to HG. OTT switched to HG2 at 8:40. SE tracking well. Flushed lower intake. Upper intake valve jammed open. Mid-section
HG: 1.097 HG2: 1.296 Found (FD)

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear  No Precipitation  Light Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column13: Control clear. No ice left in the channel.
column14: Good wading mmnt upstream of the gauge around 15 m. Some dead weeds on the left edge minor angle dues how the creeks converging. HG2 is tracking very well to th ECG. The OTT has a very large SRC. Assumed it had been frozen and liket reset when it was. Reset the OTT  Flushed the lower intake and recovered well. Good connection. Mid-section
